MAIL.MAILUTILS(1)                                             User Commands                                            MAIL.MAILUTILS(1)

NNAAMMEE
       mail.mailutils - process mail messages

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       mmaaiill..mmaaiilluuttiillss [_O_P_T_I_O_N...] [_a_d_d_r_e_s_s...]
       mmaaiill..mmaaiilluuttiillss [_O_P_T_I_O_N...] [_O_P_T_I_O_N...] [_f_i_l_e]
       mmaaiill..mmaaiilluuttiillss [_O_P_T_I_O_N...] _-_-_f_i_l_e [_O_P_T_I_O_N...] [_f_i_l_e]
       mmaaiill..mmaaiilluuttiillss [_O_P_T_I_O_N...] _-_-_f_i_l_e_=_f_i_l_e [_O_P_T_I_O_N...]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       GNU  mail  ----  process mail messages.  If --ff or ----ffiillee is given, mail operates on the mailbox named by the first argument, or the
       user's mbox, if no argument given.

       --AA, ----aattttaacchh=_F_I_L_E
              attach FILE

       --aa, ----aappppeenndd=_H_E_A_D_E_R: VALUE append given header to the message being sent

       ----[[nnoo--]]aalltteerrnnaattiivvee
              force multipart/alternative content type

       ----aattttaacchh--ffdd=_F_D
              attach from file descriptor FD

       ----ccoonntteenntt--ffiilleennaammee=_N_A_M_E
              set the Content-Disposition filename parameter for the next ----aattttaacchh option

       ----ccoonntteenntt--nnaammee=_N_A_M_E
              set the Content-Type name parameter for the next ----aattttaacchh option

       ----ccoonntteenntt--ttyyppee=_T_Y_P_E
              set content type for subsequent ----aattttaacchh options

       --EE, ----eexxeecc=_C_O_M_M_A_N_D
              execute COMMAND

       --ee, ----eexxiisstt
              return true if mail exists

       ----eennccooddiinngg=_N_A_M_E
              set encoding for subsequent ----aattttaacchh options

       --FF, ----bbyynnaammee
              save messages according to sender

       --HH, ----hheeaaddeerrss
              write a header summary and exit

       --ii, ----iiggnnoorree
              ignore interrupts

       --MM, ----[[nnoo--]]mmiimmee
              compose MIME messages

       --NN, ----nnoossuumm
              do not display initial header summary

       --nn, ----nnoorrcc
              do not read the system mailrc file

       --pp, ----pprriinntt, ----rreeaadd
              print all mail to standard output

       --qq, ----qquuiitt
              cause interrupts to terminate program

       --rr, ----rreettuurrnn--aaddddrreessss=_A_D_D_R_E_S_S
              use address as the return address when sending mail

       --ss, ----ssuubbjjeecctt=_S_U_B_J
              send a message with the given SUBJECT

       ----[[nnoo--]]sskkiipp--eemmppttyy--aattttaacchhmmeennttss
              skip attachments with empty body

       --tt, ----ttoo
              read recipients from the message header

       --uu, ----uusseerr=_U_S_E_R
              operate on USER's mailbox

              Global debugging settings

       ----ddeebbuugg--lleevveell=_L_E_V_E_L
              set Mailutils debugging level

       ----[[nnoo--]]ddeebbuugg--lliinnee--iinnffoo show source info with debugging messages

              Configuration handling

       ----ccoonnffiigg--ffiillee=_F_I_L_E
              load this configuration file; implies ----nnoo--ccoonnffiigg

       ----ccoonnffiigg--lliinntt
              check configuration file syntax and exit

       ----ccoonnffiigg--vveerrbboossee
              verbosely log parsing of the configuration files

       ----nnoo--ccoonnffiigg
              do not load site and user configuration files

       ----nnoo--ssiittee--ccoonnffiigg
              do not load site-wide configuration file

       ----nnoo--uusseerr--ccoonnffiigg
              do not load user configuration file

       ----sseett=_P_A_R_A_M_=_V_A_L_U_E
              set configuration parameter

              Informational options

       ----ccoonnffiigg--hheellpp
              show configuration file summary

       ----sshhooww--ccoonnffiigg--ooppttiioonnss
              show compilation options

       -?, ----hheellpp
              give this help list

       ----uussaaggee
              give a short usage message

       --VV, ----vveerrssiioonn
              print program version

       Mandatory or optional arguments to long options are also mandatory or optional for any corresponding short options.

